Personally we have more than enough healing items, but this is cute enough to maybe skirt around that. However-



Possible use for Foundation medical treatment is under review. Until such a time when instances of SCP-2295-1 are confirmed to have no side effects or future complications, personal use is preemptively denied by order of Site Director ████████.
附加记录：    

I am downvoting for this. I can't accept that the Foundation would allow this to be used, for two big reasons. The first being that, well, it involves the Foundation using an anomaly for non-containment things. And two, this is a really bad healing item to use. Like, sure the organs work fine, but they're still made of cloth. You can kind of notice that. Which means personnel who receive this treatment have to be treated by the Foundation for all future hospital things, which is a massive problem for secrecy.







